text.section:
The constitution or bylaws shall include:
a pledge that the employee organization accept members without regard to age, marital status, national origin, race, religion, disability, sexual orientation, or gender;
the right of members to participate in the affairs of the employee organization;
procedures for periodic elections for officers by secret ballot;
fair procedures governing disciplinary actions;
procedures for the accurate accounting of all income and expenditures;
a requirement that an independent annual financial report be produced; and
the right of members to inspect the organization's accounts.
